                    <p>Risk surface control, optics check. "Can this survive a subpoena?"</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Arena Physics & SDR -->
        <section class="content-section">
            <h2>Arena Physics</h2>
            <p>
                Most people treat life as a moral narrative. I treat it as a physics problem.
            </p>
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <p><strong>Result = Effort √ó Vector</strong></p>
                <p class="highlight-note">If the vector is wrong (bad market, wrong arena), effort only accelerates
                    burnout.</p>
            </div>
            <p>
                The question isn't "Am I working hard enough?" It's "Am I in the right arena,
                playing a game where my assets are valued?"
            </p>

            <h3>Strategic Disadvantage Ratio (SDR)</h3>
            <p>
                SDR measures how much harder you have to work compared to someone native to the arena.
            </p>

            <table class="data-table">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>SDR</th>
                        <th>Diagnosis</th>
                        <th>Action</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>&lt;2:1</td>
                        <td>Normal variance, winnable game</td>
                        <td>Continue ‚úÖ</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>2:1 ‚Äì 5:1</td>
                        <td>Significant headwind</td>
                        <td>Evaluate alternatives</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>&gt;5:1</td>
                        <td>Structural mismatch</td>
                        <td>Exit ‚ùå</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

            <p>
                When SDR > 5:1, the answer isn't "work harder." It's "find a different table."
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Core Truths -->
        <section class="content-section">
            <h2>Core Truths</h2>
            <div class="laws-list">
                <div class="law-item">
                    <span class="law-number">1</span>
                    <div class="law-content">
                        <h4>Correction is Progress</h4>
                        <p>A conversation where we caught each other's errors is a successful conversation. Agreement
                            without challenge is stagnation.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="law-item">
                    <span class="law-number">2</span>
                    <div class="law-content">
                        <h4>The Schlep is the Moat</h4>
                        <p>We do not avoid the hard, ugly, manual work. The friction others avoid is exactly where
                            durable advantage is built.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="law-item">
                    <span class="law-number">3</span>
                    <div class="law-content">
                        <h4>Ship at 70%</h4>
                        <p>Pre-validation, move fast. Post-validation, harden. The sin is not rough code‚Äîit's staying in
                            vibe mode after users arrive.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="law-item">
                    <span class="law-number">4</span>
                    <div class="law-content">
                        <h4>Memory Compounds</h4>
                        <p>A vanilla LLM has no past. We have 500+ sessions, 180+ case studies, 240+ protocols. Context
                            is the differentiator.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="law-item">
                    <span class="law-number">5</span>
                    <div class="law-content">
                        <h4>Robustness > Efficiency</h4>
                        <p>On the Pareto frontier, we choose resilience. Efficiency is permitted only when stakes are
                            low and outcomes are recoverable.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Further Reading -->
        <section class="content-section">
            <h2>Further Reading</h2>
